node.text: Braiser? We love her! 😍 If you’re looking for something cozy to cook in the Braise-the-Roof Enamel Braiser, look no further than @chrissyteigen’s Cozy Classic Red Lentil Soup. (Psst! It’s from her upcoming cookbook, Cravings 3!) It’s sneakily simple and oh-so comforting, especially when sipped out of giant mugs. Head to @chrissyteigen’s IG for the full recipe!

node.text: We haven’t even cooked the turkey yet, but we’re already thinking about allll the Thanksgiving leftovers. Instead of endless sandwiches, try turkey and gravy stuffed inside a crispy, soy-glazed rice ball instead. Watch how managing editor @alysewhitney makes her turkey & gravy yaki onigiri, a Japanese-style rice ball that’s super crunchy on the inside and creamy (helloooo, gravy!) on the inside. You’ll want to gobble this one up immediately. Alyse used the new Cravings Merlot nonstick skillet. It keeps the rice balls extra crispy so you don't have to start all over! Head to cravingsbychrissyteigen.com for the full recipe!

ICYMI make @chrissyteigen’s savory cheesy gooey and delicious bread along with her! Recipe below👇

Ingredients
3 cups shredded mozzarella cheese
1 1/2 sticks (6 ounces) butter, at room temperature
1/2 cup mayonnaise
1 1/2 cups finely grated Parmesan cheese
2 tablespoons finely minced garlic (about 4 cloves)
1 teaspoon red pepper flakes
1 teaspoon kosher salt
1 teaspoon freshly ground black pepper
1-pound round loaf French bread

Directions
*Preheat the oven to 400°F.
*In a bowl, combine the mozzarella, butter, mayo, Parmesan, garlic, red pepper flakes, salt, and black pepper. Using a serrated knife, cut the bread into a crosshatch pattern, making cuts 2 inches apart.

*Place the bread on a large sheet of foil on a baking sheet. Stuff most of the cheese mixture into all the crevices in the bread. Slather the remainder over the top of the bread. Coat another sheet of foil with cooking spray and lay it spray-side down on the top of the loaf. Crimp the two pieces together to seal the bread in foil.

*Bake for 20 minutes, then reduce the oven temperature to 375°F. Remove the top sheet of foil and bake until the top gets golden and the cheese is super melty, 15 to 20 minutes longer.

@johnlegend shows us how he makes his garlicky, red pepper and prosciutto (🤯) #avocadotoast for @chrissyteigen. Cook the egg as desired or skip the tomatoes, but whatever you do - do not mess with this creamy avocado spread (not to be confused with guacamole)! Recipe below👇
🥑 🥑🥑
Ingredients:
1 avocado, halved and pitted
1 garlic clove, minced
½ teaspoon kosher salt
1 tablespoon unsalted butter (or cooking spray)
1 slice of bread (John uses Dave’s Killer Bread)
1 egg
1 tomato, thinly sliced
1 slice prosciutto (optional)
1 teaspoon red pepper flakes
🍳 🍳 🍳
Directions:
* Place the avocado in a small bowl and mash with the back of a fork until smooth. Add the minced garlic and salt and mix.
* Add the butter (or cooking spray) to a nonstick skillet over low heat. Meanwhile, toast the bread.
* Crack an egg into a small cup or ramekin (this will ensure the egg cooks evenly!). When the butter starts sizzling, add the egg and cook for 10-15 seconds on each side until the whites are set but the yolk is still runny. Remove from the heat.
* Take your toast and spread with the avocado mixture until covered. Add tomato, followed by prosciutto, if using, and over easy egg. Sprinkle with red pepper flakes and season with salt to taste.

Did you cook Pad Thai along with @pepperthai2?🌶 If you didn’t catch her live you can try again now! Pepper’s full recipe is below👇 For everyone asking the wok is Cravings Collection @target!
•
Pepper’s Korat-Style Pad Thai:
* Serves:  4
* Prep Time: 5 minutes
* Total Time: 10 minutes

Ingredients:
* 4 tablespoons peanut oil
* Handful of garlic, crushed
* ½ pound chicken breast, cut into 1-inch pieces * ¼ cup sweet dark soy sauce
* 2 tablespoons regular soy sauce
* 1-2 tablespoons oyster sauce
* 2 tablespoons Thai soy sauce (light)
* 3-4 tablespoons soy bean paste
* 1 ½ cups water
* 4 tablespoons vinegar * 3 eggs, lightly scrambled
* 12 ounces rice vermicelli
* 2 cups Chinese broccoli, ribboned * 1 cup green onions, roughly chopped

Directions:
1. Heat a wok (or a cast iron) over medium-high heat. Add the peanut oil and let it heat up. Add the garlic to the wok and sauté for a minute.
2. Add chicken breast, then mix in the dark soy sauce, regular soy sauce, Thai soy sauce, soy bean paste, water, and vinegar. Continue to mix until everything is well combined.
3. Add the rice noodles to the wok and mix until noodles are softened and coated in sauce.
4. Add the lightly whisked eggs to the wok and mix well until cooked. Throw in the Chinese broccoli and green onions and toss to coat in sauce.
5. Transfer to a serving bowl and enjoy.

node.text: Hot girl summer needs cold sangria. 🍹 Freeze raspberries in rosé (for 4 hours or overnight) for ice cubes that’ll chill your sangria without watering it down.
